<DOC><DOCNO> AP880930-0006 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-30-88 0401EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-China-Judge     09-30 0163</FIRST><SECOND>PM-China-Judge,0167</SECOND><HEAD>``Last Emperor'' Team Working On New Film In China</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Italian film company that produced theOscar-winning movie ``The Last Emperor'' is at work on a new filmportraying a detective drama about China's 7th century mastersleuth, Judge Di.   Italian producer Franco Giovale of RVC Productions, who alsomade the ``Marco Polo'' television series, signed a contract inAug. 1987 with the China Film Coproduction Corp., said Ann Roddy, aproduction assistant for the project, in a recent interview.   Judge Di combines elements of James Bond and Sherlock Holmes ashe braves China's remote and treacherous landscape to solvebaffling crimes in a world of bandits, prostitutes, monks and cultworshippers.   The Tang dynasty detective was popularized in the West by Dutchsinologist Robert Van Gulik through his series of Judge Di novels.   No director or filming schedule has been announced for the film.``The Last Emperor,'' directed by Bernardo Bertolucci, took fiveyears to make.</TEXT></DOC>